WEBVTT

00:04:28.800 --> 00:04:32.323
And she'd start laughing, she was like,
"Yeah, I'm talking to Stephanie."

00:04:32.768 --> 00:04:36.197
AdG: At Zappos, they actually encourage
this kind of personal connection.

00:04:36.545 --> 00:04:40.450
But many workplaces don't create the space
for genuine emotional expression.

00:04:40.767 --> 00:04:42.180
Think about your job.

00:04:42.204 --> 00:04:45.466
You probably had moments
when you just faked an emotion.

00:04:45.490 --> 00:04:47.291
You plastered on a smile,

00:04:47.315 --> 00:04:50.442
you tried to sound cheerful
even when you weren't feeling it.

00:04:50.799 --> 00:04:53.462
Alicia Grandey: I always think
of the flight attendants

00:04:53.486 --> 00:04:57.090
that have to say goodbye to each
and every passenger that leaves the plane.

00:04:57.114 --> 00:04:59.114
"Goodbye now! Goodbye now!"

00:04:59.138 --> 00:05:03.319
AdG: This is Alicia Grandey, an industrial
organizational psychologist at Penn State.